race.comment: FORCEFILLY (8) was on-pace, winning a CL1 comfortably at Bathurst, and she tackled much stronger than this at Canberra following and wasn't far away. She gets in well again with the 4kg claim and has solid each-way claims. LIQUOR TALK (10) peaks here and last time was only beaten 2.2L in a CL3 at Randwick at long odds. He won here this grade three back when fresh, and the 3kg claim helps. Has to be considered. SUPAIRO (3) is also back in grade and has been knocking on the door. She is in a leading Sydney barn and gets her chance. BOOM IN THE DARK (6) disappointed two back, but the form around that would see her in the finish. Drops from a CL1 at Wagga but needs a good ride from the awkward barrier.
